R7-million was reportedly paid to outgoing City of Tshwane municipal manager Dr Moeketsi Mosola. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Human Settlements MEC Lebogang Maile wants answers over an alleged R7-million golden handshake. It was reportedly paid to outgoing City of Tshwane municipal manager Dr Moeketsi Mosola. READ: Tshwane city manager granted special leave Maile has written to Mayor Steven Mokgalapa asking for clarity on the matter. The city has granted Mosola an extension of his special leave, meaning he remains in his position until 31 August. READ: City of Tshwane, Municipal Manager part ways Mosola has been at the centre of controversy over the irregular appointment of engineering consultants Glad-Africa to help the city manage its infrastructure projects. The city says it's finalising Mosola's separation agreement.